  "texts": [
    "It takes the following steps to fit several models: First, they create several bootstrap samples, each of which functions as a distinct (almost) independent dataset selected from the true distribution.",
    "Then, for each of these samples, a weak learner is fitted, and the results are combined to build an ensemble model that has less variance than the sum of its parts.",
    "Similar to how the bootstrap samples are generally independent and identically distributed (i.i.d.",
    "), the learned base models exhibit this property as well.",
    "Finally, by ''averaging'' the outputs of the weak learners, the variance is decreased without changing the projected result."
  ],
